Encapsulation
Concept:
Bundle data and methods together and restrict direct acceses

Inheritance
Concept:
One class acquires properties of another class.
Example:
Plain text
Animal
   ↑
 Dog
Dog inherits common characteristics from Animal.

Polymorphism
Concept:
One action, many forms.
Example:
Plain text
Payment
   ↑
Credit Card Payment
UPI Payment
Cash Payment
The same operation (pay()) behaves differently.

Abstraction
Concept:
Hide implementation details and show only essential features.
Example:
You drive a car without knowing how the engine works.
